info.name: SQL GET requests
info.description:
The API GET requests. Those requests can return a **json** or a **csv**.

The variables of the request are parsed through the url. Those variables will be explained at each request *below*

Those request can be given a query parameter that specifies if **a json string or a csv file must be returned**(*in our examples we are using json format in order for the results to be more visible*)

## HTTPS response codes

*   200: Successful request
*   400: Bad request (variable parameters are invalid)
*   401: Not authorized (request send by unauthorized user)
*   402: No data (empty response)
*   500: Internal Error (every other type of error)
    

Below each of the requests is explained
